/b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Glaser, Mark (June 8, 2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://mediashift.org/2012/06/poll-how-often-do-you-take-a-break-from-technology160/\">\"Poll: How Often Do You Take a Break from Technology?\"</a>. <i>MediaShift</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">9 February</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=MediaShift&amp;rft.atitle=Poll%3A+How+Often+Do+You+Take+a+Break+from+Technology%3F&amp;rft.date=2012-06-08&amp;rft.aulast=Glaser&amp;rft.aufirst=Mark&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmediashift.org%2F2012%2F06%2Fpoll-how-often-do-you-take-a-break-from-technology160%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATechnology+Shabbat\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-NY_Times-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-NY_Times_7-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Leonhardt, David (April 18, 2017). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/18/opinion/youre-too-busy-you-need-a-shultz-hour.html\">\"You're Too Busy. You Need a 'Shultz Hour.<span style=\"padding-right:0.2em;\">'</span>\"</a>. <i>NY Times</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">7 February</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=NY+Times&amp;rft.atitle=You%E2%80%99re+Too+Busy.+You+Need+a+%E2%80%98Shultz+Hour.%E2%80%99&amp;rft.date=2017-04-18&amp;rft.aulast=Leonhardt&amp;rft.aufirst=David&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2017%2F04%2F18%2Fopinion%2Fyoure-too-busy-you-need-a-shultz-hour.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATechnology+Shabbat\" c